Spread squash in 11x7-inch microwavable dish. Add water and sprinkle with salt. Cover with plastic wrap, folding back one corner to vent steam. Microwave on High 5 minutes. Stir, recover and microwave on High an additional 2 minutes or until squash is very tender. Heat oven to 375 degrees F. Meanwhile, mix remaining ingredients and sprinkle evenly over squash. Bake 10 minutes or until granola is browned.